Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the optimization of the achievable sum-rate of a simultaneous wireless information and power transfer (SWIPT) system, which is a key topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the optimization of a relay-based communication system, which is a common topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an iterative algorithm to achieve the joint solution, which involves control and optimization techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the optimization of a full-duplex (FD) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) amplify and forward (AF) relay, which is a common topic in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes an iterative algorithm based on difference of convex programming (DC), which is a computational optimization technique.
